# linuxfromscratch

Here use virtualbox-5.1.10 to build and install USB disk LFS system.

========
Step 1. Add a user lfs.
========

./make_lfs.sh user


========
Step 2. Create rootfs.
========

./make_lfs.sh dirs


========
Step 3. Build tools.
========

./make_lfs.sh tools

========
Step 4. Mount and chroot.
========

./make_lfs.sh dirs mount
./make_lfs.sh chroot mount
./make_lfs.sh chroot

========
Step 4. Build system.
========

./make_lfs.sh system

========
Step 5. Install USB disk.
========


